results.response: The discussion delves into the theological evolution of the purpose of marriage, emphasizing the goods of marriage identified by St. Augustine: proles (children), fides (faithfulness), and sacramentum (permanence). Over time, the understanding of marriage expanded to include friendship and companionship, with the Second Vatican Council highlighting marriage as an intrinsic good that embodies unity, procreation, and sacrificial love for sanctification.
